A member of the National Governing Board of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC), Prince Kunle Oyewumi, has lamented the death of former governor of Oyo State, Otunba Adebayo Alao-Akala. Describing Alao-Akala’s death as a huge loss to Oyo State and Nigeria, Oyewumi acknowledged his contributions to the social, economic and political development of Nigeria. He stressed that the notable political figure would be greatly missed by the people of Ogbomosoland and environs. Boko Haram Abduct Mobile Police Officers In Borno Bayelsa Farmers Lament Destruction Of Farms By Open-Grazing… In a condolence message, Oyewumi, one-time Special Adviser during the regime of the former governor, prayed to God to grant the deceased eternal rest and give the people of Ogbomoso the fortitude to bear the loss. He said, “The demise of the former governor of Oyo State, Otunba Adebayo Alao-Akala, is a huge loss to the country. “Having served meritoriously in various positions in the political space, the late politician contributed immensely to nation building.